						               													<description>Crowdfunding is a game for all ages where you must get backers for your project by going to the press, events, social networks... While contingencies and Forum trolls act against you.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;COMPONENTS&amp;#10;1 Board, 1 Turn token, 10 counters X player', 30 event cards, 6 character cards, Rulebook (Spanish, English, Catalan...)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;THE BOARD HAS 4 AREAS: &amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Calendar: 40 slots, one for each campaign day. In some slots we can find modifiers to our actions that we will apply once we have the result of these. Also we can see a few special slots marked in red.&amp;#10;    Card's Slot: Place for event cards&amp;#10;    Pledge's Track: In this space you will place your player's colour tokens to indicate the amount of collected money for your campaign. If anytime you lack counters you will have to reorganize them and it is possible that you lose some contributions.&amp;#10;    Press Track: Indicate the quantity and contacts of mass media and press been interested in our campaign.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;WEEKLY PLANNING&amp;#10;The game runs through 40 days divided in weeks. Every player will choose an action to play in every day marked in white applying the pertinent modifiers. The slots marked in red indicate bank holidays and weekends, in each one we will reveal a card that affects all players and will.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the beginning of every week (slots 1,8,15,22,29 and 36) Baker and Press counters are placed in the initial position that indicates the character's card of every player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;THE ACTIONS&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Backers Search: Raise a space in your Backer's track if it is possible. &amp;#10;    Contact Press: Raise a space in your Press track if it is possible. &amp;#10;    Lucky card: Reveals the first event card and solve it (only  affects the player who makes the action) &amp;#10;    Do cash: Add in your Pledge's track 25 &amp;euro; x Backer (or use your character's card cash action) &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;WINNERS &amp;#10;All the players who finish the campaign with the fulfilled aim wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
